<HEADLINE> Lombardi Wins Seventh Stage in Spain Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Giovanni Lombardi won
the seventh stage of the Tour of Spain cycle race over
185-kilometers from Alicante to Valencia on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jeroen Blijlevens of the Netherlands finished second and
German Marcel Wust came third.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Jose Maria Jimenez retained the overall lead.
</P>
