<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, September 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian State Duma, the lower house of parliament, on
Friday confirmed Yevgeny Primakov's nomination as prime minister
by an overwhelmingly majority.
</P>
<P>
It was the third round of vote by the State Duma on premier's
nominee.
</P>
<P>
In a speech before the voting in the State Duma, Primakov said
that he would appoint communist Yury Maslyukov as first deputy
prime minister in his coming government. (Russia-Duma-Primakov)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- President Bill Clinton, in a speech to dozens of
religious leaders Friday, included Monica Lewinsky in his
statement of regret for having an improper relationship and lying
about it.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think there is a fancy way to say that I have sinned,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time he had included a direct mention of
Lewinsky, the former White House intern. (Clinton-Apologies)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodia's King Norodom Sihanouk Friday appealed
to elected parliamentarians to participate in the new National
Assembly to be convened on Sept 24.
</P>
<P>
The King extended the invitation in a letter to Prince Norodom
Ranariddh and Sam Rainsy, the leaders of the two opposition
parties of FUNCINPEC and the Sam Rainsy Party (SRP).
(Cambodia-King)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Six Irish guerilla fighters who won early release
from jail walked out of Maize Prison near Belfast on Friday under
the province's peace deal.
</P>
<P>
Three of them are Roman Catholics who sought to end British
rule of Northern Ireland, while the other three are Protestants
who fought to prolong it, according to reports from Belfast.
(Britain-NIreland-Prisoners)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- European Commission President Jacques Santer
demanded on Friday that the flight ban on Yugoslav carriers be
observed by all European Union (EU) member states.
</P>
<P>
"The decision taken by the 15 (EU member states) has to be
implemented by all 15 countries," Santer said in a written
statement. (EU-Yugoslavia-Flight Ban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- President Laurent Kabila's troops have retaken the
eastern town of Lubutu in the Democratic Republic of Congo after
intense bombardments, a report reaching here from Kinshasa said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Lubutu, located on the highway between the third city of
Kisangani and eastern town of Bukavu bordering Rwanda, returned to
the embraces of Kabila's loyalists with 45 rebels killed and 19
taken prisoner, a communique from the Information Ministry was
quoted by state television as saying. (Congo (K)-Town Seizure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif Friday
declared that the parliament will decide the country's position on
signing the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT).
</P>
<P>
"Parliament represents the true aspiration of people of
Pakistan and it is the parliament which will decide our position
on the CTBT," Sharif told reporters after presiding over the
parliamentary party meeting. (Pakistan-PM-CTBT) 
</P>
</TEXT>
