<HEADLINE> Taliban to Hand Over Bodies of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Islamic
Taliban militia Friday said they would hand over bodies of Iranian
diplomats to the International Committee for Red Cross (ICRC)
after Iran's formal request.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to hand over the bodies to Iran through ICRC
after receiving formal request from Iran," Taliban's envoy Saeedur
Rahman Haqqani said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban authorities found nine bodies of Iranian diplomats,
who had been missing in the northern Afghan city of Mazar-e-Sharif
since it fell to Taliban on August 8.
</P>
<P>
Iran had reported 10 diplomats and one official reporter
missing after the Taliban raided the Iranian consulate in
Mazar-e-Sharif. The fate of the remaining two Iranians is still
unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
