<HEADLINE> China's Envoy On Question of Taiwan's UN Reentry  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The raising of the
question of so-called "Taiwan's representation at the United
Nations" is a brazen attempt to challenge General Assembly
Resolution 2758 (XXVI), China stressed here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the General Committee of the 53rd session of the
General Assembly, Qin Huasen, Chinese Permanent Representative to
the United Nations, said at the instigation of the Taiwan
authorities and in disregard of the U.N. Charter, the General
Assembly Resolution, principles of international law and the
decision of the General Committee in the past five years, this
year a handful of countries had once again raised the question of
so-called "Taiwan's representation at the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin said the proposal, in essence, is part of the
activities to split a sovereign state and create "two Chinas" or
"one China, one Taiwan " at the solemn organization of the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
Qin said such an illegal act constitutes a grave encroachment
on China's sovereignty and brutal interference in China's internal
affairs, and it has trampled wantonly on the U.N. Charter, General
Assembly Resolution 2758 (XXVI) and Principles of international
law.
</P>
<P>
Qin aid the Chinese Government and people express strong
indignation at and condemnation to such act, and China is strongly
opposed to inscribing item 166 of the draft agenda in the agenda
of the 53rd session of the General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Qin Expressed the hope that the General Committee will continue
to uphold justice, safeguard the purposes and principles of the
U.N. Charter, General Assembly Resolution 2758 (XXVI) as well as
the principles of international law, and support the position of
the Chinese delegation.
</P>
</TEXT>
