<HEADLINE> Finnish Foreign Minister Talks Finnish-Chinese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Foreign Minister
Tarja Halonen on Friday praised the role China plays in the world
and stressed the importance of a closer Finnish-Chinese ties.
</P>
<P>
The social and economic progress China made in the past 10
years benefited not only itself but the world at large. China is
playing an ever increasing role not only in Asia but in the world
as well, the foreign minister told Xinhua before her China trip
from September 13 to 18.
</P>
<P>
China is a responsible partner in the world community, which is
fully demonstrated in its restrained reaction to the nuclear tests
carried out by India and Pakistan earlier this summer.
</P>
<P>
Five finnish ministers are to visit China this fall. And the
two presidents' summit in Beijing immediately after the 15th
National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party fully
demonstrated the character of the ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
She said she was looking forward to meet her Chinese
counterpart in Beijing, and exchange views with Chinese leaders on
such commonly interested issues as the two countries' ties and
Asia's political and economic situation. 
</P>
