<HEADLINE> 16th Commonwealth Games Open in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The 16th Commonwealth
Games were officially opened by Malaysian Supreme Head of State
Tuanku Ja'afar here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
There are 16 sports at the 11-day games -- athletics, aquatics,
badminton, boxing, cricket, cycling, gymnastics, men's hockey,
women's hockey, lawn bowl, netball, rugby, shooting, squash,
tenpin bowling and weightlifting.
</P>
<P>
The games attracted some 5,000 athletes and officials from 70
countries. The athletes will run for a total of 291 gold medals in
the 16 sports.
</P>
<P>
Before the official opening, competition in some of the sports
like badminton, cricket, hockey and squash had already started.
</P>
</TEXT>
