<HEADLINE> India Declares 1999-2000 "Visit India Year" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 11 ( Xinhua) -- In a bid to promote
tourism in India, the government announced Friday to observe
1999-2000 as "Visit India Year", the Press Trust of India
reported.
</P>
<P>
Some activities had already identified and the government was
in the process to work out other details for the event, Union
Tourism and Parliamentary Affairs Minister Madanlal Khurana said
in Hyderabad, capital of mid-south Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the annual convention of Travel Agents Association
of India, the minister said travel industry had to play a key role
in packaging of tourism products and its marketing through
innovative methods.
</P>
<P>
Khurana said that his ministry was trying to facilitate private
investment in tourism sector by providing essential support
services and incentives.
</P>
<P>
Tourism in India has been severely hit following the nuclear
tests last May with foreign visitors declining in number and many
hotels rooms vacant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
