<HEADLINE> Central Bank Chief Confirmed by Duma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma
confirmed Viktor Gerashchenko as Chairman of the Central Bank with
273 voting for and 65 against, while two abstaining, on Friday
evening, according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Friday, Yeltsin accepted the resignation tendered by
former head of Central Bank Sergei Dubinin and named Gerashchenko
as head of the CB.
</P>
<P>
Before the voting on his nomination Gerashchenko said at the
State Duma that the situation in the banking system is very
complicated, but it reflects the poorly-considered economic policy
which did not aim at the development of the national production.
</P>
<P>
He requested the State Duma to dismiss the current members of
the Central Bank Board and immediately decide on the membership of
the Bank board.
</P>
<P>
Gerashchenko warned that "a full collapse of the banking system
will occur next Tuesday if the State Duma does not take a
decision on the membership of the Central Bank Board today."
</P>
<P>
At his request the State Duma dismissed on Friday the Central
Bank's Board of directors. Now a draft resolution on the new Board
will be prepared on Monday after consultations at the Duma budget
committee. It will be discussed at a Duma plenary meeting on
Wednesday, September 16.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Central Bank Board are nominated by the State
DPB297NBB211I11TSQL02:5102:511441
VHK234NBB211I11TSQL02:5102:511446
Duma for a period of four years on the presentation of the Central
Bank Chairman coordinated with the president.
</P>
<P>
In Gerashchenko's opinion, a reason for the financial crisis is
the economic policy; the statement of the government and the
Central Bank of August 17 averted investors from Russia.
</P>
<P>
He favors a close contact between the Central Bank and the
government and the Duma control over the activity of the Central
Bank. 
</P>
