<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The government of the
Republic of Kazakhstan "fully supports" the position of the
government and people of the People's Republic of China in
safeguarding their sovereignty and territorial integrity, a
senior diplomat from Kazakhstan said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan opposes the question of so-called "Taiwan's
representation at the United Nations" raised by a small number of
countries, the representative said at the General Committee of the
53rd Session of the General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The government of the Republic of Kazakhstan recognizes the
representatives of the government of the People's Republic of
China are the sole legitimate representatives of China and its
people as a whole, he said.
</P>
<P>
Together with Kazakhstan, representatives from Argentina, Sri
Lanka, Iraq, Kuwait, Georgia and Mexico also took the floor to
support Beijing on the Taiwan issue. The General Committee will
resume its meeting Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The General Committee of the 53rd Session of the General
Assembly met Friday morning to adopt the agenda and allocation of
items for the current session.
</P>
<P>
The General Committee has, for five years in a roll since 1993,
refused to put the so-called question of "Taiwan's representation
at the United Nations" in the agenda of the General Assembly.
