<HEADLINE> Portuguese-Speaking Nations Urged to Promote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese-speaking countries
should strive to realize economic integrity through tightened
cooperation among the community, so to face the economic
globalization.
</P>
<P>
Marcollino Moco, Executive Secretary of Portuguese-Speaking
Community said here Friday that more attention should be paid to
multi-lateral cooperation among the community.
</P>
<P>
He said that cooperation among the the community members are
mostly bilateral now, which is not good for a community in which
many member nations are underdeveloped. He advocated multiple
cooperation among the community.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese-Speaking Community, established in 1996, groups
Angola, Brazil, Mozambique, Portugal, Guinea Bissau, Sao Tome And
Principe, and Cape Verde with a population of 200 million people.
</P>
<P>
While saying that he cherished good hope on enterprises in the
member nations, Moco said that each country should find their own
advantage in the cooperation among the community for the future
participation in global economy.
</P>
<P>
Moco, the former Angolan Prime Minister, arrived in Luanda
Tuesday for a four-day visit to Angola. 
</P>
