<HEADLINE> Tanzania Urged to Open Another Camp for DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 11 (Xinhua)-- Tanzania has been asked
to provide another site where a refugee camp can be built to
cater for refugees fleeing the civil war in the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Head of United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees
sub-office in Kigoma, Jean Durieux, said Friday that the influx
of Congolese refugees is alarming.
</P>
<P>
Although the present camp at Nyarugusu, in Kasulu district,
west Tanzania's Kigoma Region, still has room for more refugees,
there is a need to have another contingency site, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Nyarugusu Camp is specifically set to accommodate
Congolese refugees and it can accommodate about 20,000 people.
</P>
<P>
DRC is currently locked in a civil war in which the rebels
want to topple the government of President Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
By Thursday, Kigoma Region had 4,405 refugees from DRC. The
average daily number of new arrivals stands between 150 and 200.
</P>
<P>
Besides the Congolese refugees, Kigoma also hosts Burundian
refugees.
</P>
<P>
According to Durieux, the region has received 2,364 Burundian
refugees since August 1. The Burundian refugees camp is at
Mtendeli in Kibondo district in Kigoma and has the capacity of
accommodating about 10,000 refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
