<HEADLINE> Animal Exhibition Opens in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A special exhibition opened
today in Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan province, to
show lives of different animals.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 specimens of beast, bird, fish, insect and reptile
are on display.
</P>
<P>
Organizers from the provincial science association said that
the show is to enhance the public's awareness of protecting the
wild animal.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is home to 58.9 percent of the animal species in China
and known as the "kingdom of animal". Some of the animals,
including the golden monkey, are on the verge of extinction.
</P>
