<HEADLINE> Jones Clocks Fourth-Fastest 100 Meters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Marion Jones of the
United States recorded the fourth-fastest time ever over 100
meters on the second day of the World Cup here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Jones, assisted by a following wind of 1.1 meters a second,
clocked 10.65 seconds to win her second World Cup title in as
many days.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Jones clocked the third-fastest time ever over 200
meters, winning in 21.62. 
