<HEADLINE> Redgrave Wins Record Eighth World Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- British rowing legend Steve
Redgrave won a record eighth world championship title in Cologne
on Saturday as he wrested the gold medal with Britain's coxless
four.
</P>
<P>
The crew, also including James Cracknell, Tim Foster and
Matthew Pinsent, clocked a winning time of five minutes 48.06
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The same four won the event last year in Aiguebelette in
France.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Redgrave also won gold medals at the last four
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Redgrave won seven titles in the coxed pairs between 1981 and
1991.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Redgrave is only one of five athletes to
capture four successive Olympic golds.
</P>
<P>
Redgrave vowed to row on until the 2000 Sydney Olympics
despite being diagnosed with diabetes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
