<HEADLINE> Besenyei Claims First Day of Aerobatics Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Peter Besenyei of Hungary
cashed in on his flair for music to claim victory on the first
day of the China Cup Aerobatics FAI Grand Prix here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Besenyei garnered 8.374 points to finish first among the nine
participating pilots, with Russia's Nikolai Timofeev second on
8.266 and another Russian Viktor Tchmal third on 8.199.
</P>
<P>
"All the pilots' performance are fantastic," said chief judge
Quintin Hawthorne. "They are very similar in style except
Besenyei, whose interpretation of the accompanying music was
better."
</P>
<P>
Some ten thousand spectators came in for this spectacular
show, almost doubling the number on Friday, which was marred by
heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
"It's incredible," said hotel servant Yuan Jun, who is a a
ircraft model fan himself. "Even my models can't be flown in that
way."
</P>
<P>
The tournament, hailed by FAI president Eilif Ness as the
greatest ever festival of aerobatics, attracted the top 24
finishers of last year's world aerobatics championships.
</P>
<P>
The pilots will go on to tour the Chinese cities of Nanjing,
Jinan, Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Zhengzhou, Wuhan and Changsha.
</P>
