Berti Vogts quit as Germany's head coach on Monday, said he was
not sure whether he would seek re-election at the next DFB
congress in October.
</P>
<P>
The 73-year-old Braun went for Erich Ribbeck, who has plenty
of experience but lacks the pedigree of his predecessors after
the preferred candidates were unavailable or turned down the
offer to follow Vogts.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey released on Friday, 87 percent of the
5,289 fans who took part felt Braun should step down. 
