<HEADLINE> Congo (K) Rebels Accused of Aiding UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A UNITA force in Angola has
captured Maquela do Zombo, a border town in northern Angola under
the help of the rebels from neighboring Democratic Congo.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the Tutsi-led rebels used at least five 160 mm
cannons to bomb the town Thursday, ofvering aid to the fighters
of the opposition movement of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), the Journal of Angola charged
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The government's national police were forced to retreat to the
neighboring Zaire Province after putting up a short resistance.
</P>
<P>
Maquela do Zombo is situated in Uige Province, about several
dozens of kilometers south of the Angolan-Congolese border.
</P>
<P>
Fernando Canga, Vice Governor of Uige`Province, said the UNITA
force is advancing on Damba City, the provincial town of Northern
Uige. He accused UNITA fighters of mounting frequent military
raids on his province, and killed 13 civilians in one on Puri
Village, kidnapping several government officials recently.
</P>
<P>
Angola and Congo (K) share about 2,000 kms of border line.
UNITA has allegedly got quite a number of logistic bases inside
Congo (K) for provision and diamond smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Tutsi Banyamulenge rebels which revolted on August
2 in eastern Congo (K) and UNITA fighters allegedly support each
other, and this is why the Angolan government has send troops to
intervene and prop up Congolese President Laurent Kabila in
western Congo, said the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
