<HEADLINE> Pakistan Has Made No Decision on CTBT: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has not yet
decided to sign the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) and will
take an appropriate decision after a debate by the joint sitting
of the parliament, a Foreign Office spokesman said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan has not taken any decision in this respect," the
spokesman said while commenting on press reports concerning the
matter.
</P>
<P>
He said the parliament is debating on the CTBT and would make
recommendations to the government on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The government can, afterwards, "take an appropriate decision
in the larger interest of the country," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said that "Pakistan is not opposed to the treaty as such,
but will not sign it under coercion." 
</P>
