<HEADLINE> China's Second Investment, Trade Fair Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The five-day China Second
Investment and Trade Fair ended today with 2,766 projects
contracted with a total investment of 19.7 billion U.S. dollars,
including overseas investment of 14.2 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, the fair attracted not only major national commercial
organizations, but also such well-known international businesses
as Motorola, Nokia, Mobil, Panasonic, Sony, Siemens and the World
Bank.
</P>
<P>
Despite the Asian financial crisis, the projects contracted in
this fair have increased by 30 percent over last year, including
213 projects each with an investment of more than 10 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In terms of investment by region, the middle and western parts
of China have been active as well as the coastal areas. The
largest investments are for infrastructure and industrial
projects, agriculture, tourism and real estate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
