<HEADLINE> Seminar Opens on Agricultural Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A three-day seminar on the
development of agricultural technology opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the China Society of Agriculture, the seminar
attracted more than 150 agro-technicians and officials to discuss
the problems China faces in the development of agricultural
technology and measures to solve them.
</P>
<P>
China has made great achievements in the development of
agricultural technology in the past decades and even taken a lead
in the world in some fields, such as research on hybrid rice and
genetically engineered insect-resistant cotton, said a society
official.
</P>
<P>
Further development of the sector faces some problems, he said,
citing inappropriate technology and the research structure.
</P>
<P>
China also needs to raise its agricultural technology levels to
solve problems such as how to feed its 1.2 billion people and
develop an environmentally friendly economy, the official said.
</P>
