<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 12:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Launch Massive Military Maneuver Near </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Following its threat to take
revenge on the Afghan Taliban militia, Iran announced Saturday to
launch its biggest military maneuver involving 200,000 troops near
its eastern border with Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, the army's commander of
land forces Abdolali Pourshasb said that 40 percent of the three
divisions have been deployed along the border during the past
month under the command of supreme leader and Commander-in-Chief
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
He said the troops would remain in the border areas after the
week-long maneuver, which would be carried out in an area of 5,000
square kilometers in the northeastern province of Khorasan and the
southeastern province of Sistan and Baluchestan.
</P>
<P>
He said the maneuver, code-named Zoulfaqar 2, would start at
the end of September. The participating troops which include the
elite forces, armored, mechanized and artillery units would stage
the exercises with the support of the air force.
</P>
<P>
It will be the second massive maneuver that Iran has staged
since early August when tensions erupted between Iran and the
Afghan Taliban militia over the fate of 11 Iranian diplomats
missing in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran recently announced that nine of the Iranian diplomats who
worked in the Iranian consulate in Mazari Sharif in northern
Afghanistan were killed when Taliban took over the city on August
8. It added that two of the diplomats escaped the Taliban killing,
but Taliban said all the Iranian diplomats were dead.
</P>
<P>
On September 1, the Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps held a
maneuver with the participation of 70,000 troops in Khorasan
province and then deployed the troops in the area to build up
pressure on the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
Pourshasb termed the Zoulfaqar 2 maneuver as a "routine
military exercise" without any intention to pose threat to any
country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the objective of the maneuver was to guarantee
security and stability in the border areas and defend the
country's territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Pourshasb ruled out any possible conflict with the Taliban
during the maneuver. But he warned that if Iran feels any threat,
the army would give strong response to it.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Iranian army would carry out any order
issued by the country's leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
