<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Invest in Improving Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Chongqing declared a program today to improve its worsening
environment.
</P>
<P>
The program will use 640 million yuan (80 million U.S. million
dollars) to improve farmland, plant trees and construct water
conservation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing, with a population of 30 million, is the largest
industrial and commercial center on the upper reaches of the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The unrestricted cutting of trees and reclaiming of wasteland
were major factors triggering this summer's floods on the
Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing's decision is part of an overall plan to better the
Yangtze's environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
