<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Financial Secretary to Visit Europe, U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Financial
Secretary Donald Tsang will later this month pay a three-week
visit to Europe and the United States to exchange views with other
financial leaders on the restoration of order and stability in the
international financial markets.
</P>
<P>
He will explain the government's recent moves to reintroduce
stability and a level playing field in the money and stock
markets.
</P>
<P>
Tsang will leave Hong Kong on September 27 for Frankfurt and
then move on to Munich, The Hague, Amsterdam, Washington, New York
and Boston, back to London and then on to Edinburgh. He is due
back in Hong Kong on October 20.
</P>
<P>
He described his forthcoming visit as important, saying that he
has three objectives.
</P>
<P>
"First is to raise for discussion in a higher profile the
question of greater transparency and disclosure of interests in
market activities and some discipline on monitoring international
fund flows.
</P>
<P>
"Second, I wish to gather first-hand knowledge on the
development of Euro dollar and its implications for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Third, I will endeavor to dispel any misunderstanding or
doubts in the minds of our overseas investors and other
interlocutors about our recent counter-activities in the stock and
futures markets," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said he will reinforce again the HKSAR government's
determination to maintain the linked exchange rate under its
currency board system and reiterate its commitment to free and
open markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
