<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong-Guangdong News-Photo Exhibition Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of news
photographs taken by journalists of Hong Kong and Guangdong of
China's mainland opened here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region attended the opening ceremony of the
exhibition, which was jointly organized by the Hong Kong
Federation of Journalists and the Guangdong Association of
Journalists.
</P>
<P>
A total of 300 photographs are displayed, with each side of
Guangdong and Hong Kong providing 150 of them. They recalled major
events happened in Guangdong and Hong Kong around the period
before and after Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
The photographs are divided into six themes -- the Return of
Hong Kong to China; Social Events; Political and Economic Events;
Culture and Sports; Daily Lives and Exchange Between Guangdong and
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They were chosen out of the pictures provided by most of the
Hong Kong media and major newspapers in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will close on September 14. A collection of the
displayed pictures will be published and the pictures will be
showed in Guangzhou later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
