<HEADLINE> Ranariddh to Seek Advice From King on Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Prince Norodom Ranariddh
said Saturday he will meet his father King Norodom Sihanouk to
seek a resolution to the current political crisis in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh said the King, who resides in the northern town of
Siem Reap, will meet him on September 16.
</P>
<P>
"The King is the only person who can help the main three
political parties settle the current crisis in Cambodia," said the
prince, who is leader of the FUNCINPEC party.
</P>
<P>
Tensions in Cambodia mounted Ranariddh and Sam Rainsy, leader
of the self named Sam Rainsy Party refused to recognize the
results of the election. They claim that irregularities and fraud
were perpetrated during the election.
</P>
<P>
They also vowed to boycott the parliamentary session and turned
down an offer to form a coalition government with Second Premier
Hun Sen, whose party won 64 of the 122 National Assembly seats.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh reaffirmed Saturday that the opposition would not
give up their demands despite a warning from the King. The King
said that if they boycott the inauguration of the new parliament,
their privileges as members of the parliament will be deprived.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
