<DOCNO> XIE19980912.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNESCO, ASEAN Urged to Consolidate Peace in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Participants in a symposium
here Saturday urged UNESCO and ASEAN to reinforce their
cooperation through the undertaking of joint endeavors, which can
contribute to the consolidation of peace and security in Southeast
Asia.
</P>
<P>
A statement on peace in Southeast Asia on the eve of the third
millennium was adopted by the symposium after ending two-day
discussions.
</P>
<P>
The progress made in the field of cooperative peace in the
framework of ASEAN should be consolidated through the mobilization
of all institutions and individuals who are committed to building
a lasting peace in Southeast Asia, in particular on the occasion
of the year 2000, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The year 2000 has been proclaimed International Year for the
Culture of Peace by the General Assembly of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was held here at the joint initiative of the
United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization
(UNESCO) and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to
strengthen cooperation between two organizations in the building
of peace. UNESCO officials and delegations from ASEAN member
countries attended the symposium.
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed the hope that the symposium "will
contribute to strengthening the foundations for peace in the third
millennium for all the nations of Southeast Asia".
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting with participants of the symposium on
Friday, Indonesian President B.J. Habibie expressed the hope that
the discussions in this symposium will yield significant
contribution to the Culture of Peace Year.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the effort to enhance cooperative peace at the regional
level will eventually bring all of us closer to the creation of
world peace on the basis of common justice and prosperity," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the symposium, UNESCO and ASEAN signed an
agreement of cooperation between two organizations in order to
facilitate social and cultural development in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
