<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandans Without IDs, No Jobs in Govt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Ugandans without national
identity cards will not be employed in any public office across
the country under a new citizenship and immigration control bill
now before Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The bill tabled by Minister of Internal Affairs Tom Butime
this week requires every Ugandan to register with the national
citizenship and immigration board to be issued with an identity
card, the New Vision paper said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Under the bill, any Ugandan citizen who fails to get such a
card without reasonable reasons will be prone to a fine up to
200,000 Shillings (160 U.S. Dollars) or three-month imprisonment
or both.
</P>
<P>
The report, however, did not mention the reasons for issuing
such identity cards.
</P>
<P>
The bill provides for acquisition of citizenship, compulsory
registration of all Ugandans, issuance of national identification
numbers and cards to citizens.
</P>
<P>
Reports here said security is one of the main reasons for this
move. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
