<DOCNO> XIE19980912.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Trade Official Criticizes U.S. for Irrational Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Chinese
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation said the strict
regulations by the United States on Chinese wood packaging are
"irrational" and severely hinder normal Sino-U.S. trade and
bilateral economic cooperation, especially China's exports to the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that China has expressed a deep concern
about the regulations signed by the U.S. Secretary of Agriculture
on Friday, and reserves the right to further reactions.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that China opposes trade protectionism of various
forms, the spokesman expressed hope that the United States would
consider the regulations prudently, and that quarantine
departments and experts of both sides would conduct sincere and
effective cooperation in seeking a proper settlement to safeguard
the general situation of the development of bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Sino-U.S. trade in recent years has
grown rapidly and the two countries have become important trade
partners.
</P>
<P>
A new development momentum has emerged in bilateral economic
and trade relations, especially after heads of state of the two
countries exchanged visits, the spokesman said, adding that the
maintenance and development of such momentum requires efforts from
both sides.  
</P>
</TEXT>
