<HEADLINE> Wenger Worried over Arsenal's Fate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- English premier league club
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger has revealed he has major concerns
about the possibility of new owners taking control of the team.
</P>
<P>
London-based media company Carlton have been linked with a 275
million pounds buy-out of the Highbury giants.
</P>
<P>
But Wenger, who has yet to sign a two-year extension to his
contract, is worried that business-oriented directors are
"impatient" and can interfere with the playing side of the club.
</P>
<P>
And he hinted he might even quit the Gunners if a new board
made his job more difficult, according to local reports on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"If you are having problems you must have patience," he said.
</P>
<P>
"That's not easy if you don't know football.
</P>
<P>
"The impatience has grown already and people coming in might
become even more impatient, " he added. 
</P>
