<HEADLINE> Norwegian, Mozambican Unions Step up Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Norway will help Mozambique
train its trade union leaders, back its improvement of services
to its members and step up personnel exchange and support to each
other.
</P>
<P>
This was contained in an agreement signed between Finn
Troresen, President of the Norwegian Printers Syndicate and
Joquim Fanheiro, General Secretary of the National Union of the
Workers of the Chemical, Rubber, Paper and Printing Industries
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Fanheiro disclosed that the Norwegian Syndicate has offered
70,000 U.S. Dollars in aid to his union for the past two years
and will render support to the third congress of the union which
will open in Maputo next year.
</P>
<P>
Troresen said after the signing ceremony that he hoped the
existing fine cooperation between the two unions will be
consolidated and expanded to other fields.
</P>
<P>
He said his syndicate which has a history of 116 years will
decide on the amount granted to the Mozambican union in the
coming three years.
</P>
<P>
Troresen who led a delegation in a week-long visit to Maputo
will leave for home later Saturday. During his stay here, he had
talks with Mozambican leaders of trade unions, and toured some of
the printing houses, the Revolutionary Museum and the Arts
Palace in the capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
