<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Thai Banks Downgraded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The downgraded banks were Bangkok Bank, Krung Thai Bank, Thai
Farmers Bank, Siam Commercial Bank and Thai Military Bank. A major
Thai financial institution, the Industrial Finance Corporation of
Thailand, was also downgraded.
</P>
<P>
"Moody's noted that the stability of Thailand's banking system
continues to be undermined by the financial crisis, as escalating
loan loses erode bank's capital and earnings," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"The extreme fragility of the system inevitably threatens even
those banks that have raised considerable amounts of new capital
this year -- Bangkok Bank and Thai Farmers Bank," said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
It said even those banks needed to gain significant new
capital to fully restore solvency.
</P>
<P>
However, Moody's Investors Service placed the long-term debt
and financial strength ratings of the Bank of Asia on review for a
possible upgrade. The decision reflected the acquisition of a
majority interest in the bank by ABN Amro of the Netherlands.
</P>
