<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonded Warehouse in Northeast China's Shenyang Coty to be Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The first bonded warehouse
for Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, will
be built in the city's high-tech development zone with approval
from the China General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
The bonded warehouse will give tax breaks on imported materials
needed by processing enterprises and overseas-financed companies
in China for manufacturing export products.
</P>
<P>
This warehouse, the only one approved by the General
Administration of Customs in Shenyang, will have an area of 66,000
square meters and will cost 11 million yuan. It will be completed
and operational by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
As a major economic, transportation and cultural city of
northeast China, Shenyang has more than 500 companies that have
been given autonomy to organize exports independently, with a
combined trade volume of one-billion U.S. dollars. Half of this
consists of re-exports made with client-supplied or imported
materials.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the establishment of the bonded warehouse will
help advance the city's foreign trade by providing
overseas-financed enterprises, and export commodity processing
enterprises, with simplified tariff procedures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
