<HEADLINE> EU to Further Support Bulgaria's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
further help Bulgaria with its integration into EU and civil
structure and administration reform, said EU Commissioner Hans
Van Den Broek on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Broek, who was on the second day of a two-day visit to
Bulgaria, expressed his satisfaction at a news conference over the
close cooperation between Bulgaria and the EU in the process of
integration.
</P>
<P>
He discussed the details of Bulgaria's progress to join the
European Union during the meeting with Bulgarian President Peter
Stoyanov. He described the exchange of views as "constructive."
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's structural reform, regional co-operation and the
crisis in Russia were also on the agenda of their meeting.
</P>
<P>
"The structural and administrative reforms need special
attention," he said. "I shall not hesitate to voice my full trust
in the progress Bulgaria has made so far, and our support for
furthering this progress."
</P>
<P>
The EU commissioner for relations with Central and Eastern
European countries was satisfied with Bulgaria's role in regional
affairs and its cooperations with neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about regional security, Van Den Broek favored the
Bulgarian-Romanian cooperation in building a second bridge across
the Danube river.
</P>
<P>
At present, Romania and Bulgaria still have difference on the
location of the bridge.
</P>
<P>
On Friday morning, Van Den Broek toured central Rousse, a city
of Bulgaria on the Danube, and inspected road construction and
repairing work done under the Beautiful Bulgaria Project, which is
funded by the U.N. Development Program and the EU. 
</P>
