<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Party Expresses Anguish at Cruel Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil United
Liberation Front (TULF) has expressed outrage and anguish at the
cruel killing of P. Sivapalan, mayor of Jaffna, in a bomb
explosion in the city Friday, reports reaching here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sivapalan displayed extraordinary commitment to democratic
values and public service by responding to the request to succeed
former mayor Yogeswaran who was assassinated in May this year, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
In June this year, Sivapalan was sworn in as mayor of Jaffna,
Sri Lanka's Northern Province capital, over 400 kilometers from
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
He was the legal secretary of the TULF which got the largest
number of seats in the Jaffna Municipal Council in local elections
held in January this year.
</P>
<P>
The Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam, which has been fighting a
war for independence since 1983, has rejected the January
elections on Jaffna Peninsula. 
</P>
