<HEADLINE> Illegal Immigrants Repatriated From Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 12 (Xinhua)-- Border police in Fujian
Province in east China recently accepted 225 illegal emmigrants
repatriated from Mexico and redoubled efforts to search for
"snake-heads", or groups which organize illegal border crossings.
</P>
<P>
The illegal immigrates, 212 males and 13 females seeking to
find employment in the United States, were swindled between
1996-1997.
</P>
<P>
The individuals, each payed between 35,000-40,000 US dollars,
were subjected to harsh conditions while shuttling through a
number of ports prior to arriving in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
They were eventually arrested at the U.S.-Mexican border,
according to Fujian police officials who said the intensified
battle against illegal emigration introduced early last year has
reduced the number of people involved in related activities by
about 60 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
