<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Investigation into Killings of Iranians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The United States on
Friday called for an urgent investigation into the killings of nine
Iranian diplomats in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"We join with other members of the United Nations Security
Council in calling for an urgent investigation into these crimes
so that the perpetrators can be brought to justice," State
Department spokesman James Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
The killing of nine Iranian diplomats was announced by
Afghanistan's Taliban militia on Thursday, which said its
fighters, acting without order, had killed nine of 11 Iranian
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
Since the disappearance of the 11 Iranian diplomats in
Afghanistan, Iran has been stepping up a huge military military
buildup on the border between the two countries, and asked the
United Nations to condemn the killings. It also demanded the
arrest and prosecution of those responsible for the killings.
</P>
<P>
The United States has been trying for the past year to improve
relations with Iran while it has become more hostile toward the
Taliban since the bombing of its embassies in Kenya and Tanzania,
which it alleged was masterminded by exiled Saudi financier Osama
bin Laden who now lived in Afghanistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
