<HEADLINE> China to Produce 32 Million Bikes in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- China will produce 32 million
bikes this year to meet rising market demand, according to the
China Light Industry News.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted the China Bicycle Association as saying
that market demand currently stands at 20 million
domestically-produced bicycles and some 13 million imported units.
</P>
<P>
China has trimmed bicycle production since 1996, due to
shrinking market demand and the accelerated development of the
automobile manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
The average Chinese family owns 2.32 bicycles, according to a
recent association survey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
