<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Export Revenues Drop in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's coffee export
revenues dropped almost 22 percent to 192 million U.S. dollars,
compared to the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Coffee Exporters Association said Friday that the
total volume of coffee exports amounted to 1.6 million 60-kilo
bags in August, 30 percent more than in the same month of
1997. But due to the lower price in the international market, the
export revenues decreased by 22 percent.
</P>
<P>
The association predicted that the Coffee exports are expected
to reach 17 million or 18 million bags this year, about 40 percent
more than last year. 
</P>
