<HEADLINE> U.S. Pledges to Work with Russia's New P.M. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The United States said
Friday that it will work with Russia's new Prime Minister, Yevgeny
Primakov, as long as his nation's economic reforms continued.
</P>
<P>
"We'll work with him," White House spokesman P.J. Crowley said
in response to the Russian State Duma (lower house of
parliament)'s confirmation of Primakov's nomination earlier in the
day.
</P>
<P>
"He's putting together his government," Crowley said. "A
significant challenge confronts him in terms of the Russian
economy and we will work with the government provided that they
continue their policies of economic reform," he added.
</P>
<P>
On Primakov's experience in economic reforms, the spokesman
said, "He's been a part of the government. Obviously he's been a
part of discussions regarding international assistance and
support. As part of the government there has been a clear platform
to support economic reform. We certainly hope that that will
continue.".
</P>
<P>
Igor Ivanov, Russia's first deputy foreign minister, will
succeed Primakov as foreign minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
