<HEADLINE> New York Liberty Fires Coach Nancy Darsch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The New York Liberty, who
failed to make the WNBA playoffs after reaching the finals in
1997, announced today they will not renew the contract of head
coach Nancy Darsch.
</P>
<P>
"We appreciated Nancy Darsch's efforts as head coach of the
Liberty, however, at this time we feel the team needs to move in
a new direction," said club vice president and general manager
Carol Blazejowski. "We wish her all the best in her future
endeavors."
</P>
<P>
Darsch compiled a 35-23 record in her two seasons with the
Liberty. She guided the team to a 7-0 start en route to a 17-11
mark in the league's first season in 1997. New York beat Phoenix
in the playoffs, but lost a one-game championship to the Houston
Comets.
</P>
<P>
This year, the Liberty compiled a 18-12 record, but missed the
post-season after losing to the Detroit Shock on the final day of
the regular season.
</P>
<P>
New York, unlike other teams in the league, stayed with a
veteran lineup throughout the season. Darsch spent 12 seasons at
Ohio State after seven years as an assistant coach at Tennessee.
She posted a 223-125 record, including four Big Ten championships
and seven NCAA tournament appearances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
