<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan: Question of Taiwan's Reentry to UN Must </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly,
in its resolution 2758 (XXVI) adopted at its 26th session, clearly
stated the representatives of the Government of the People 's
Republic of China are the only lawful representatives of China to
the United Nations, Pakistan reiterated here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the General Committee of the 53rd session of the
General Assembly, Ahmad kamal, Pakistan's Ambassador to the United
Nations, said this historical verdict clearly settled the question
of the representation of the Chinese people at this world body
once and for all.
</P>
<P>
Kamal said Pakistan, like most others, welcomes the historical
ruling of the General Assembly, and it believes any attempt to
reopen the review of the issue constitutes a serious violation of
the Charter of the United Nations and it is confident that the
member states will reject any attempt to undermine the Charter of
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Kamal said despite the historical verdict of the General
assembly, numerous attempts have been made in the past few years
to reopen the issue, and as a result, the wasteful debate takes
place every year in the General Committee, consuming the General
assembly's energy and time which should be devoted to the more
substantive issues.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador stressed this is why the General Assembly must
bury this issue once for all so that the energy and attention can
be directed to the more pressing problems facing the world
organization.
</P>
<P>
Kamal said Pakistan firmly believes that China is a sovereign
member state of the United Nations,and Taiwan, which is a part of
China, has no right whatsoever to join the United Nations, and
there is no need to review the resolution 2758 any more.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador expressed his most sincere hope that it is for
the very last time that the General Committee meets to go through
the avoidable agony of the consideration and debate on the subject
on which the decision of this year will on doubt be identical to
what it has been in the previous years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
