<HEADLINE> Sailor Who Threatens to Blow up Nuke Submarine Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A sailor who killed eight
fellow servicemen and threatened to blow up a nuclear-powered
submarine in Severomorsk, Murmansk region in northern Russia was
killed early Saturday, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The sailor, identified as 19-year-old Alexander Kuzminykh who
barricaded himself in the torpedo section of a nuclear-powered
submarine of the Northern Fleet, was shot dead at 00:20 local time
(21:20 GMT Friday) during an attempt to seize him, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Early Friday morning, Kuzminykh left the submarine and went to
the mooring, where he seriously wounded a sentinel and seized his
automatic rifle. He also wounded an officer who tried to stop him.
</P>
<P>
One of the wounded apparently died later.
</P>
<P>
Kuzminykh then returned to the submarine and killed five
sleeping fellow sailors. He took two other sailors hostage and
killed them later.  
</P>
