<HEADLINE> Flash: General Committee Excludes Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The General Committee of
the 53rd Session of the U.N. General Assembly on Friday decided not to
put the so-called question of "Taiwan's representation at the United
Nations" in the agenda for the General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
This is the sixth consecutive refusal by the General Committee
since 1993 to include the issue in the General Assembly agenda. 
</P>
